# drift-baseline — populated by `scripts/sync-codex-fork.sh` (Task 4).
#
# Purpose:
#   Snapshot of SHA256 hashes for every skill in `plugins/morkit/skills/` at
#   the moment the codex fork was last synced. `scripts/check-codex-drift.sh`
#   compares current hashes against this baseline to warn (never fail) when
#   `skills-codex/` is out of date.
#
# Format (one entry per line):
#   <relpath-from-skills/>:<sha256>
#
# Constraint: <relpath> MUST NOT contain ':' (used as field delimiter by the
# awk parser in check-codex-drift.sh). Sync script will reject paths violating
# this. SKILL.md paths under skills/ are unlikely to need ':' in practice.
#
